reviews.text: This location was in a convenient location for me when I visited Stuttgart in mid-February 2023. Ordered the Gnocchi Zucchini Zafferano	and Tiramisù for take out. When I went to pickup my order I had problems locating the entrance. Decent food.

The overall experience was ok. The entrance is not easy to find, a waiter asked us to sit at the bar without commenting how long we need to wait. We did not wait long, got a descent table for 3. The restaurant was relatively full, but not too loud. Orders were fast, personnel nice and friendly. The food was really fat. Pizza literally swimming in oil and fish in a fatty sauce. Taste was ok, so it was ok. But not more in my opinion
The place is full but the waiter so friendly to give us a table. All I can say for a chain restaurant the food taste so good. Definitely will come again.
The foods are superb: the pizza is large and delicious; the pasta is great too.

Amazing pizza! They are highly recommend!

The cocktails however are not quite recommended.

I have tried Avocado Chicken bombs and the Chicken shawarma poutine.
The Avocado chicken was fried chicken in a crispy cover, filled with an avocado filling. The filling tasted nice but didn't really have avocado flavor.
The Chicken shawarma fries were nice, the Chicken was nicely cooked and flavorful. However, I found it to be salty. It would have been better if they didn't put salt on the fries since you can add salt yourself later anyway.
There was a small line because ordering, you first have to pay and then wait for your order to be prepared. Forks, salt and pepper are available later at a separate table.

Rainbow bowl is delicious, with tender chicken chunks. Fries is average though. In convenient location within Milaneo Shopping Centre. Self service ordering kiosk and waiting time is short as I went during off peak period.
Absolutely delicious, with minimal waiting time. This was my second visit and I am sure I will definitely visit again and try other options (as there are so many). Highly highly recommended!

Either it wasn’t my lucky day or this is the normal in this place. First all free tables were dirty with sources and food drops from previous users, we fetched the tissue and cleaned the mess up may be because it’s located in a shopping mall?

Then i ordered a salad bowl (please see pictures below) and it came without dressing, i went back to ask for the salad dressing and all i was given was salt and pepper. :(( to be honest i didn’t enjoy the salads i couldn’t eat them half way without the dressing. I give it 2 stars for the chef he/she did a great job with the chicken.

Quite good fries! Tried Frittenwerk two times so far! For me as a poutine newbie...Yeah I liked it! Well if you are a crunchy fries fanatic you should stick to the housefries or for me....the garlic fries! Oh yes! And if you like the mushy saucy goodness go for one of their poutines! Something different! 😉

Great place and not only burgers   ;)

Better come with company!

I had burger with camamber - so yummy,  highly recommended.  In evening getting busier and more laud but atmosphere is good
Quick food once ordered but service can be slow. Great with many vegan options. Need some unsweet drinks like ice tea.

We are regular customers at the HiG at Milaneo but were sent to this location because they closed early. Food was a total disappointment. Burger was lukewarm, cheese not even close to being melted, when complained I got a new one, not any warmer, with cold avocado sauce and HiG sauce which I asked NOT to be on. Sweet potato fries were cold and chewy instead of crispy. Our waitress was fantastic, great customer service but her manager refused any refund and charged the full price. Management can definitely learn a lot from their employees. Will avoid this HiG location going forward. Too bad being treated like that after having been regular customers at other locations for so long.

Amazing burgers! Finally what you can really call a gourmet burger. Came here on a Saturday evening for dinner without any reservations. Place opens pretty late (like 12am) and we were having very late dinner, so a great options for late diners. Staff was a little absent and we had to call folks to get our order, but food was delicious. One of the best burgers I have had in a while. We ordered the chicken burger and veggie burger and both were amazing. The sauces they provide on the table were also very delicious. Overall highly recommended when craving good burgers!

A very interesting hamburger network in Stuttgart. In this unit the team was very attentive and helpful, speaking and offering menu in English.

There are interesting promotions and combined with snacks and drinks around 18 euros.

editorial_summary.overview: Straightforward pan-Asian eatery furnishing sushi, stir-fried noodles & baked tofu, plus bubble tea.

reviews.text: Do not accept the card if you per charge less than 15€. I was there twice, a young guy he didn't even smile to customer. The food was ok. But quite pricy
Anonymous sauteed noodles (#02 on the menu) to stay filled until dinner. The spicy sauce was normalized to German standards, that is not hot at all. And too bad they don't accept cards below 10 euro
Affordable prices, good food, you can select which sauce you desire, location is convenient, as well.
Very average Asian takeaway shop. Not much in it, can't expect too much when most of the menu items are less than €5
Food was fantastic, but too sad that we cannot pay with card below 15 Euros.

editorial_summary.overview: Beers, wines & shots, plus snacks like paninis, in a lively, bohemian bar popular with students.

reviews.text: Went three times while visiting Stuttgart with a friend. Saturday lunchtime quiet but nice, evening crazily busy (!) and monday evening a nice in between. Excellent bar staff and nice clientele. Definitely recommend!

Small little tavern. Quaint and nothing really special. Apparently a popular hang out because there was no where to sit. Not really down for drinking with barely legal little kids. Still blows my mind how young they get to drink here and I think they all go to the tavern.
Nice place to start your night life in Stuttgart, not a great ambience but good for students and impromptu meeting.
A very nice surprise. The place is always full with young people. Is in the center of the city on a street bot open to traffic. A place to go if you want to meet some young people in the city
One of the most happening bars in Stuttgart city center. Resonable prices and good (but always crowded) atmosphere! Always good to be there.

editorial_summary.overview: Relaxed pub with table football & stickers on the walls, serving up beer, burgers & snacks.

reviews.text:
Prices are lowest in Stuttgart? 🤗
a pub, not stylish cool people, but the real people. Sone singles too. Seems very flexible, and bar staff has time to smile and say some words to all clients. This is cosy athmosphere!!
it’s nice, complete menu, prices are ok. It really fills up and there’s a lot of cig smoke, if you are sensible to it/don’t like the smoke it’s not the place for you. Nice overall!

An institution in Stuttgart. A melting pot of different audiences who share one desire: One last beer. It's open almost 24/7 and a famous spot for table football. Having entered, you dive into the smoking area. The non-smoking area is separated by a glass door. The crowd is mixed with a majority on liberal, left-wing side. Well-used toilets can be found in the basement. Although the clear focus is on beers and drinks you can get solid snacks as well. Try the leek stew with pepper sausage.

I did not personally like the place where smoking is allowed inside a closed premise.
It felt like most of the people around the area are coming to this place when all other pubs are closed for after parties...
I was refused entry simply because the security guy said he didn’t trust me because my people come there to cause trouble
